        <content type="html" xml:base="https://www.jimmyff.co.uk/gallery/homemade-christmas-cards-2021/">&lt;p&gt;I decided to feature Elphie on our card this year, it was a little challenging as at the time I needed to send this off to the printers (late november), we didn&#x27;t actually have her yet!&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;




&lt;img alt=&quot;Elphie&quot; title=&quot;Elphie&quot; src=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.jimmyff.co.uk&#x2F;processed_images&#x2F;card1.cc1580164f351022.webp&quot; srcset=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.jimmyff.co.uk&#x2F;processed_images&#x2F;card1.3ded2dab7ee78155.webp 512w, https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.jimmyff.co.uk&#x2F;processed_images&#x2F;card1.cc1580164f351022.webp 1024w, https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.jimmyff.co.uk&#x2F;processed_images&#x2F;card1.b85a551d56b5b753.webp 2048w&quot; class=&quot;&quot; &#x2F;&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Once again I added little craft gems to the cards to add a little bling. Neil made a lovely poem for ths inside.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;




&lt;img alt=&quot;card2&quot; title=&quot;card2&quot; src=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.jimmyff.co.uk&#x2F;processed_images&#x2F;card2.02399b45b4edd2cb.webp&quot; srcset=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.jimmyff.co.uk&#x2F;processed_images&#x2F;card2.7cbbc8ae64483b36.webp 512w, https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.jimmyff.co.uk&#x2F;processed_images&#x2F;card2.02399b45b4edd2cb.webp 1024w&quot; class=&quot;&quot; &#x2F;&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This year we supported: &lt;a href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.samaritans.org&#x2F;&quot;&gt;The Samaritans&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
</content>
        
